Package com.mycompany.anothercam.StudentCommitteeApplicationManager

Class CampCommitteeReport

java.lang.Object
com.mycompany.anothercam.StudentCommitteeApplicationManager.CampCommitteeReport
public class CampCommitteeReport extends Object
Represents the CampCommitteeReport Object and the following assistance methods. A CampCommitteeReport can be run multiple times depending on the number of reports to be made.

    • writeInCSV

      public boolean writeInCSV(ArrayList<Camp> tempCampArray, ArrayList<Camp> campArray, User cookie, FileOutputStream streamOut, DateFormatter dateFor, String filename, boolean printOnlyCreate) throws IOException
      Runs the Student Camp Committee Report which is to be formatted to CSV.
      Parameters:
      tempCampArray - the temporary CampArray which the new camp object is stored.
      campArray - The ArrayList containing the camp Array to be printed out (Contains all camps)
      cookie - the User Object (A Student) which the requested user creates the Report
      streamOut - FileOutputStream object used to write information into the csv file.
      dateFor - DateFormatter object used to format any dates required.
      filename - String object where csv information will be saved into.
      printOnlyCreate - boolean to check if need to print the camp which the staff in charge created.
      Returns:
      the boolean value whether the CSV Report is saved or not.
      Throws:
      IOException
